  <<<reporter-issue-body>>>
  ### Full Maven coordinates
  
  org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core:11.0.18
  
  ### Additional context and logs
  
  Latest Spring Petclinic fails at runtime because Tomcat reflectively introspects protocol methods.
  
  Tested with:
  - spring-projects/spring-petclinic
  - Spring Boot 4.0.3
  - org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core:11.0.18`
  -  GraalVM 25.0.2
  
    ```text
  MissingReflectionRegistrationError:
    Cannot reflectively invoke method
    org.apache.coyote.AbstractProtocol.getProperty(java.lang.String)
  ```
  
    After fixing that one method, the same pattern exposed more missing methods/classes:
  
    ```text
    org.apache.coyote.AbstractProtocol.getName()
    org.apache.coyote.http11.AbstractHttp11Protocol.isSSLEnabled()
  ```
    Was solved locally by registering hints:
  
   ```text
  hints.reflection().registerType(AbstractProtocol.class,
  MemberCategory.INVOKE_PUBLIC_METHODS);
    hints.reflection().registerType(AbstractHttp11Protocol.class,
  MemberCategory.INVOKE_PUBLIC_METHODS);
  ```
  
    Equivalent reachability metadata would be roughly:
  
  ```text
    {
      "reflection": [
        {
          "type": "org.apache.coyote.AbstractProtocol",
          "allPublicMethods": true
        },
        {
          "type": "org.apache.coyote.http11.AbstractHttp11Protocol",
          "allPublicMethods": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ``
  
  ### GraalVM version
  
  GraalVM 25.0.2
  
  ### Operating system
  
  Linux
  
  ### CPU architecture
  
  AMD64 (x86-64)
